                <head>No. 117.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Fish</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hoffman</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1876-04-28">
                            <hi rend="italic">April</hi> 28, 1876</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="flushleft">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hoffman</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Chargé, London:</hi>
                </p>
                <p>Counsel on <hi rend="italic">habeas corpus</hi> seems impracticable in present
                    condition of the case. You will present to Lord Derby copy of eight sixty-four,
                    with a note referring to your previous oral communication thereof, and stating
                    that you do so under instructions, in a final hope of still preserving the
                    treaty, and in the further hope that he may see therein sufficient cause to
                    prevent the discharge of Winslow, and to order his surrender under the tenth
                    article of the treaty of eighteen forty-two, in accordance with the requisition
                    of this Government.</p>
                <p>You will further state, in substance, that although the United States does not
                    recognize the statute of eighteen seventy as controlling extradition under our
                    treaty, still, as Great Britain claims to be governed thereby, you hope that his
                    lordship will see in the twelfth section authority for his intervention to cause
                    the surrender in accordance with the treaty.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>FISH, <hi rend="italic">Secretary</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
